After hearing arguments from both sides, the court reserved its judgment. Kejriwal was arrested on June 26, accused of potentially influencing witnesses.
title: Excise case: SC to deliver key verdict on Kejriwal bail pleas tomorrow

description: OpenWeb, an Israeli software firm, is embroiled in a leadership dispute after founder-CEO Nadav Shoval challenged the board's decision to appoint Tim Harvey as new CEO. Shoval claims this move breaches his contract and damages the company. Despite this, OpenWeb supports Harvey’s interim appointment to maintain growth and stability.
title: Drama at Israeli startup, new CEO announced; old says he will not leave

description: Seven family members died when a 400-year-old fort wall collapsed onto their home in Datia, Madhya Pradesh. The incident occurred early Thursday morning, and rescue operations faced delays due to heavy rain and narrow access roads. Local authorities have been criticized for their slow response.
title: 7 dead after 400-year -old fort wall collapses in Madhya Pradesh

description: Maoist organizations report losing 5,249 insurgents in the last two decades due to heightened police aggression. The central committee's booklet details significant casualties among high-ranking members and impacts on state forces. Despite facing operational challenges and increased surrenders, they plan to mark their 20th anniversary from September 21 to October 20.
title: Over 5,000 Maoists, including 1,000 women ultras, killed in 20 years

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized the BJP-led Madhya Pradesh government after a woman was gang-raped at gunpoint in Indore, pointing out poor law and order. He highlighted concerns over increasing crimes against women. Priyanka Gandhi Vadra also targeted Prime Minister Modi, questioning his efforts to ensure women's safety across India.
title: 'Society and govt should be ashamed': Rahul after friend of Army officers gangraped

description: A suspicious bag was found at the protest site of junior doctors in Kolkata's RG Kar Medical Hospital. Security forces cordoned off the area while junior doctors continued their sit-in over the alleged rape and murder of a young medic, demanding justice and enhanced security measures for women health professionals.
title: Bomb scare: Suspicious bag found at RG Kar Medical College and Hospital

description: Shawn Laval Smith, a homeless man, has been convicted for the brutal murder of UCLA student Brianna Kupfer in 2022. He stabbed her 46 times while she worked alone in a Los Angeles furniture store. The jury found him guilty of murder and using a deadly weapon. A sanity phase will now determine his mental state during the attack.
title: 'Hunting for a woman alone': Homeless man stabbed US student 46 times

description: Norfolk Southern Corporation dismissed CEO Alan Shaw and terminated Executive Vice President Nabanita C Nag after discovering their inappropriate relationship. Mark R George has been appointed as the new President and CEO, effective immediately. Jason A Zampi will serve as acting Chief Financial Officer during this transition period.
title: CEO fired over 'inappropriate relationship' with India-origin lawyer

description: Small finance banks have increased fixed deposit rates to over 8% for two-year tenures, challenging larger banks like SBI and HDFC Bank. This move seeks to attract more deposits amid growing alternative investments.
title: FD rates above 8%: Banks are offering higher rates than SBI, HDFC

description: Ishan Kishan made a surprising appearance in India C's playing XI for the Duleep Trophy's second round, despite being previously ruled out with a groin injury. His unexpected inclusion, without any official update from the BCCI, has sparked confusion and speculation among fans and analysts regarding his recovery and future in Indian cricket.
title: Ishan Kishan's unexpected Duleep Trophy comeback: What happened?

description: A Chinese man died just 13 days after undergoing a dental procedure that involved extracting 23 teeth and inserting 12 implants in one day at Yongkang Deway Dental Hospital. The incident has led to widespread outrage, an investigation, and concerns from medical experts about the safety and ethics of such extensive procedures.
title: Man dies of heart attack following removal of 23 teeth and 12 implants

description: In Cuddalore district, five individuals, including a four-year-old boy, lost their lives when their car collided head-on with a lorry near Chidambaram. They were returning to Kumbakonam from Chennai. The lorry driver, who was speeding, abandoned his vehicle and fled after the accident. Authorities are investigating the incident.
title: 5 crushed to death in head-on collision between car and lorry near TN

description: Bangladesh's Shoriful Islam will miss the two-Test series against India due to a groin injury. The Bangladesh Cricket Board announced a 16-member squad for the tour, with Litton Das expected to keep wickets. The first Test is scheduled for September 19 in Chennai, and the second Test will be held on September 27 in Kanpur.
title: Bangladesh announce Test squad for India tour

description: Bharti Airtel CEO Gopal Vittal has proposed a unified effort among telecom operators to tackle Unsolicited Commercial Communications (UCC).
title: What Airtel CEO Gopal Vittal wrote in letter to Jio, Vi, Tata Tele and BSNL CEOs

description: Republican vice-presidential candidate JD Vance criticized Taylor Swift after she endorsed Kamala Harris. In an Instagram post, Swift praised Harris and humorously called herself a 'childless cat lady.' Vance responded on Fox News, claiming that Swift is disconnected from the problems of average Americans, despite her urging followers to research before voting.
title: 'We admire Taylor's music but ... ' JD Vance on Swift supporting Harris

description: BJP IT chief Amit Malviya linked Rahul Gandhi's comments on Sikh rights during his US visit to a recent blast in Chandigarh. Malviya accused Gandhi of making false statements that could incite unrest. The explosion caused property damage but no casualties. Investigations are ongoing, with suspicions pointing towards a Pakistan-based Khalistan terrorist.
title: BJP suggests link between Rahul's remarks and Chandigarh blast

description: Eight men have been detained in Uttar Pradesh's Kushinagar district for kidnapping and gang-raping two orchestra dancers at gunpoint. The victims were forced into vehicles and taken to a house where the crime occurred. Police confiscated illegal firearms, ammunition, and vehicles from the suspects, who were apprehended after an encounter.
title: 2 orchestra dancers kidnapped at gunpoint, gangraped in UP

description: The Punjab & Haryana High Court ruled for protection of  life and liberty of two judicial officers in an extra-marital relationship but dismissed them administratively. The Supreme Court reinstated the woman officer and reconsidered the male officer's case, ultimately upholding his termination. He is entitled to back wages from April 20, 2022, until a fresh termination order on April 2, 2024.
title: Supreme Court pulls up Punjab & Haryana HC for sacking judicial officer over 'affair'

description: On the anniversary of 9/11, victims' families gathered at ground zero. President Biden, former President Trump, and Vice President Harris set aside political differences to pay respects. Some relatives urged action on Saudi involvement and justice for Khalid Sheikh Mohammed. The event also included a visit to the Flight 93 National Memorial in Pennsylvania.
title: Watch: Trump and Harris shake hands again at 9/11 memorial

description: A Pakistani father installed a CCTV camera on his daughter's head to monitor her movements and ensure her safety. The woman's video interview explaining this unusual security measure has gone viral online. She states that her father is acting as her security guard, especially after a recent murder incident in Karachi raised safety concerns.
title: Pakistani man installs CCTV camera on daughter’s head, internet calls it ‘SheCTV’

description: During the 1st T20I match between England and Australia, Josh Hazlewood deceived Liam Livingstone by showing an off-cutter grip but bowling a full pace delivery. This led to Livingstone's dismissal for 37, leaving England at a precarious position of 108/6 in their chase of 180 runs, resulting in a loss by 28 runs.
title: Watch: How Josh Hazlewood 'foxed' Liam Livingstone to get his wicket

description: Two people died, and seven others are trapped under debris after a 400-year-old fort wall collapsed in Datia district, Madhya Pradesh. Neighbours rescued two individuals, while rescue teams continue efforts to save the remaining victims. Continuous rain is suspected to have weakened the wall's structure.
title: 3 dead, 7 trapped after 400-year-old fort wall collapses in MP

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) has expressed concerns over a recent meeting between Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Chief Justice of India DY Chandrachud during Ganpati Chaturthi. Rajya Sabha MP Sanjay Raut questioned the appropriateness of such meetings, suggesting it could raise doubts about judicial impartiality, particularly in ongoing cases involving the Uddhav Thackeray group.
title: Sena case pending, CJI should recuse himself: Raut on PM-Chandrachud meet

description: Authorities in Bahraich, Uttar Pradesh, are ramping up efforts to catch a sixth 'killer' wolf following another attack that left a woman seriously injured. This incident comes after an 11-year-old girl was also attacked. The Forest Department has deployed cameras in likely wolf habitats to monitor and capture the remaining animal.
title: 50-year-old injured in wolf attack in Bahraich; search on for sixth 'killer'

description: Sculptures of Queen Elizabeth II, Prince Philip, and two corgis were recently unveiled in Northern Ireland's Antrim Castle Gardens. While some viewers appreciated the statues in person, social media users criticized their likeness to the late Queen. The bronze sculptures were created by artist Anto Brennan and commissioned by Antrim and Newtonabbey Borough Council.
title: New sculpture of Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip divides netizens

description: Persistent rain has severely impacted the only Test between Afghanistan and New Zealand in Greater Noida, marking four consecutive days without play. This match, Afghanistan's first Test at their adopted home ground near New Delhi, risks being abandoned. The venue’s inadequate facilities have come under scrutiny for failing to handle prolonged adverse weather conditions.
title: Afghanistan vs New Zealand Test in Noida faces complete washout

description: As the IPL mega auction nears, speculation mounts about Rohit Sharma's future with Mumbai Indians. Former cricketer Aakash Chopra suggests that Rohit's time with the franchise may be ending after he was replaced by Hardik Pandya as captain for ther last season. Chopra speculates that Rohit could be released or traded.
title: Rohit Sharma's IPL future with MI: Ex-India cricketer feels he will...

description: India's upcoming Test series includes matches against Bangladesh and New Zealand at home, followed by the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia. To ensure a place in the World Test Championship final, India must keep their win percentage above 60%, needing at least five wins and one draw from their next ten Tests.
title: EXPLAINED: What India need to qualify for WTC final

description: Malaika Arora's father Anil Mehta passed away on Wednesday, September 11. It is alleged that he died by suicide and now a report suggests that he had called his daughters saying 'I'm tired', before his demise!
title: Malaika Arora's father told her 'I'm tired' before alleged suicide

description: Hurricane Francine made landfall in Louisiana as a Category 2 storm, causing power outages for about 190,000 customers and severe flooding. With winds near 100 mph, the storm hit Terrebonne Parish and is expected to bring heavy rain and potential flash flooding as it moves inland toward Mississippi. Residents are advised to stay indoors.
title: ​​Hurricane Francine hits Louisiana with destructive winds, causing power cuts to over 190,000 customers​​

description: Prince Harry will mark his 40th birthday on September 15 by spending a weekend trip with close friends, as Meghan Markle stays in California with their children. Reports indicate Harry is feeling disillusioned with life in the US and reconnecting with old UK friends. He remains active in philanthropic endeavors.
title: Prince Harry to celebrate 40th birthday away from Meghan Markle

description: The Australian government has revoked medals from commanders whose units were implicated in alleged war crimes in Afghanistan between 2005 and 2016. Defence minister Richard Marles made this decision following the Brereton report, which exposed unlawful killings by elite special forces. This move aims to address past wrongs and uphold military standards.
title: Australia decides to strip commanders' medals for war crimes

description: Amazon's Great Indian Festival Sale 2024 is anticipated to begin around September 29, aligning with Flipkart's Big Billion Days sale.
title: Amazon Great Indian Festival 2024: Likely sale dates, bank offers and more

description: Assamese actress Sumi Borah and her husband were detained by the Special Task Force for their involvement in a multi-crore online trading scam. Borah announced her intention to surrender due to defamatory media coverage and assured full cooperation with the investigation. A lookout circular was issued after they failed to appear for questioning.
title: Stock trading scam: Assamese actress Sumi Borah, husband detained

description: Several areas in Delhi and the National Capital Region saw rainfall on Thursday, with more expected until Friday. The Indian Meteorological Department has issued a yellow alert, warning of possible waterlogging and traffic disruptions. Gusty winds up to 30 kmph are also predicted. Rainfall is forecasted for Uttarakhand, East Rajasthan, and Uttar Pradesh during the week.
title: Delhi-NCR wakes up to rain; brace for more as IMD issues 'yellow' alert

description: Vinesh Phogat, after being disqualified from the Paris Olympics, has joined the Congress party and filed her nomination for Haryana Legislative Assembly Elections. Contesting from Julana Constituency, she declared assets including three cars and a plot in Sonipat. Her political entry follows her dissatisfaction with support during the Olympics, which concluded in August.
title: Vinesh Phogat owns 3 cars, repaying a loan, has Rs 1,95,000 cash

description: Two individuals hurled a low-intensity explosive at a house in Chandigarh's Sector 10, targeting a retired Punjab Police SP. The blast caused minor damage but no injuries. Authorities suspect gangster Harwinder Singh Rinda's involvement. Investigations by police and NIA are ongoing, with one auto driver detained for questioning.
title: Low-intensity blast at Chandigarh house, NIA to probe

description: A Pakistani father has attached a CCTV camera to his daughter's head to ensure her safety after a recent violent incident in Karachi. The unusual protective measure has gone viral on social media, sparking debate. While some commend the father's dedication, others humorously question its practicality.
title: 'SheCTV camera': Pakistani father installs CCTV on daughter's head

description: A patient at Gandhi Hospital in Hyderabad allegedly assaulted a female junior doctor. Hospital staff intervened and handed him over to the police. The patient, suffering from seizures, continued having them even at the police station. Both police and institutional FIRs are being filed by authorities.
title: Female junior doctor assaulted in Hyderabad hospital

description: Nagamangala faced violent incidents including stone pelting and arson, leading to prohibitory orders and increased police presence. District-in-charge minister N Chaluvarayaswamy visited the site, promising strict action against those responsible. Union Minister HD Kumaraswamy blamed Congress's appeasement politics for the unrest, alleging it was a preplanned attack targeting a specific community.
title: K'taka: Kumaraswamy blames appeasement politics over communal flare up

description: Opposition parties have criticized the police probe into a crash involving an Audi owned by BJP state chief Chandrashekhar Bawankule’s son Sanket. They allege lapses in registering the FIR and claim coercion to withdraw the complaint. The incident resulted in injuries to two scooterists and delayed police response.
title: Nagpur Audi crash probe: Maha BJP chief’s son Sanket called after 14 hours

description: Individuals from Hyderabad are being lured to Laos with false job promises and then coerced into cybercrime activities. A 23-year-old victim detailed his three-month ordeal involving electric shocks and confinement before escaping back to India. The Telangana cyber crime police have initiated an investigation into these incidents.
title: Youth caught in Laos cyber crime web, face electric shocks, daily torture

description: The Indian cricket team faced pre-series mind games from Australia during their 2003-04 tour. Captain Sourav Ganguly's impressive 144-run innings at The Gabba helped India recover from early setbacks and draw the first Test. This strong performance signaled India's determination and set a competitive tone for the series. That day at the Gabba, Ganguly truly led India from the front with the bat and sent out a strong message to the Aussies that India was not going to be pushovers in the series.
title: When Ganguly's Gabba heroics set the tone for an enlivening series

description: Thousands of protesters in Shimla clashed with police over an allegedly illegal mosque construction in Sanjauli. Despite prohibitory orders, the protest escalated into violence, resulting in injuries and detentions. Himachal's public works minister confirmed that if found illegal, the mosque would be demolished while ensuring adherence to legal protocols.
title: Shimla mosque row: HP govt confirms demolition if found illegal

description: Junior doctors in Kolkata extended their protest by rejecting a second invitation from the Bengal government for talks. They insisted on conditions like a larger delegation and live telecast of discussions. The government urged them to return to work as per the Supreme Court's directive, expressing frustration over their refusal.
title: Jr doctors reject 2nd talks offer with Mamata, set fresh conditions

description: More than a dozen candidates encountered health issues during the excise constable physical efficiency test in Jharkhand. Conducted across six centers, several participants required medical attention but recovered swiftly after treatment at medical camps and local hospitals. Officials are ensuring daily reports on hospitalizations.
title: 16 fall ill at Jharkhand excise fitness test

description: A man set fire to an Ola Electric showroom in Kalaburagi after experiencing unresolved issues with his new electric scooter. The blaze destroyed six scooters, resulting in damages exceeding Rs 8 lakh. Mohammad Nadeem has been arrested and placed in judicial custody. Fire safety personnel quickly extinguished the flames, preventing any casualties.
title: Watch: Irked over snags in e-scooter, buyer torches Ola showroom

description: In the first T20I at the Rose Bowl, Travis Head scored an explosive 30 runs off one over from Sam Curran, propelling Australia to a total of 179. Head's quickfire innings of 59 off just 23 balls laid the foundation for Australia's victory. England faltered in their chase and were bowled out for 151, handing Australia a comfortable win.
title: 4,4,6,6,6,4: Travis Head smashes 30 runs off Sam Curran's over - Watch

Govt plans to build 62,500km of rural roads by 2029

Congress names 40 more candidates, Surjewala son gets Kaithal ticket

description: After Argentina's 1-2 loss to Colombia in a FIFA World Cup qualifier on Tuesday, goalkeeper Emiliano Martínez is accused of slapping a TV cameraman in Barranquilla. The cameraman claims Martínez hit his camera while he was filming. Colombia’s sports journalists’ association has requested FIFA to take disciplinary action against Martínez.
title: 'He slapped me': Argentina goalkeeper assaults a cameraman - Watch
Bangladesh 'urges' pause in Durga puja activities during azaan, namaaz
Caste census not 'Mandal vs kamandal' issue: Rahul Gandhi

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi has set an ambitious goal of tripling India's electronics manufacturing to $500 billion in six years. At SEMICON India 2024, he emphasized India's aim to become a global semiconductor leader with significant investments. Modi also pointed out growing partnerships with Japan, Singapore, and the US in this sector.
title: PM Modi sets target of $500 billion for electronics production in next 6 years

description: The ICC Men's ODI World Cup 2023 significantly impacted India's economy with a contribution of USD 1.39 billion, driven by tourism and media exposure. The event drew record crowds and created thousands of jobs, highlighting India's potential as a premier host for global sports events. The World Cup is expected to have long-term benefits too.
title: ODI World Cup 2023 boosts India's economy by Rs 11,637 crore: ICC
SP shifted after Hindu outfits demand action over Ratlam row
Impasse on as Bengal junior doctors junk 2nd govt invite for talks
BJP slams Rahul Gandhi after Pannun backs his remarks on Sikhs
Biryani row: Administration moves boy to new school, to waive Rs 37k in fees

description: Protesters in Shimla's Sanjauli area defied prohibitory orders and clashed with police over an allegedly illegal mosque construction. The confrontation led to injuries and detentions. Himachal Pradesh's public works minister stated that the mosque would be demolished if found illegal by the Shimla municipal commissioner's court. The case has been pending for ten years.
title: Mob demanding razing of 'illegal' Shimla mosque clashes with cops, 10 hurt

description: On Thursday, South Korea's military reported that North Korea launched an unidentified missile off its east coast. This event follows a similar incident in May when North Korea fired an unidentified ballistic missile into the East Sea, also known as the Sea of Japan. According to the Japanese coast guard, the projectile from May fell into the sea.
title: North Korea fires ballistic missile into eastern waters, South Korea says

description: Tensions erupted in Nagamangala, Karnataka during a Ganesh procession when miscreants threw stones at devotees, sparking a clash. Police used mild force and tear gas to disperse the crowd. Ban orders were issued under CrPC 144, and additional police forces were deployed to regain control. Devotees demand the arrest of those responsible.
title: Communal violence erupts in Karnataka during Ganesha idol immersion
IIT-Guwahati academic affairs dean quits amid stir over student suicide'

description: Australia triumphed over England by 28 runs in the first T20 international at Southampton. Travis Head’s aggressive innings of 59 off just 23 balls set the tone for Australia’s total of 179. Adam Zampa’s economical spell and timely wickets from Josh Hazlewood restricted England to 151 all out, despite a brief fightback from Liam Livingstone and Sam Curran.
title: 1st T20I: Head, Zampa star as Australia beat England by 28 runs

description: The Union Cabinet has expanded the Ayushman Bharat Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (AB-PMJAY) to cover all senior citizens aged 70 and above. Eligible seniors will get a health cover of up to Rs 5 lakh per year. This move aims to provide accessible and affordable healthcare for elderly citizens across India.
title: 70+ citizens with private cover can also avail PMJAY: Centre

description: The Centre has requested a review of a Supreme Court decision permitting states to levy royalties and taxes on extracted minerals and mineral-bearing land. This could result in a financial burden of up to Rs 1.5 lakh crore for PSUs and private industries. Madhya Pradesh joins as co-petitioner, citing public interest concerns.
title: Centre seeks review of SC's mineral royalty judgment

description: Delhi High Court has unveiled a new section on its website called Humour in Court, showcasing light-hearted courtroom moments. Acting Chief Justice Manmohan also launched Delhi High Court WhatsApp Services and an e-Museum. These initiatives aim to reduce courtroom tension and preserve historically significant case records, encouraging a lighter atmosphere among judges and lawyers.
title: Witty moments in Delhi courtrooms to now go online

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for September 12, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today: Read your today's astrological predictions
